        You define an Entity â†’ maps to a database table.
        You create a Repository interface â†’ extends JpaRepository<Entity, IdType>.
        Spring auto-generates the implementation at runtime using Hibernate.

these are just interfaces.
The beauty of Spring Data JPA is that you donâ€™t implement them manually â€” Spring Boot + Hibernate generates the implementation at runtime for you.

ğŸ” How does it work?
    When your app starts:
        Spring scans for all @Repository interfaces that extend JpaRepository.
        For each of them, Spring creates a proxy class (runtime implementation).
        The proxy class internally uses Hibernate EntityManager to talk to the database.

    So when you call:
        parkingLotRepository.findById(1L);


    Spring routes it like this:
        ParkingLotRepository (proxy) â†’ EntityManager â†’ Hibernate â†’ PostgreSQL